    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-05-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-05-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="106"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d106">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-05-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 15, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 262.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch No. 345, of March 23 last, reporting that Yu Hsien, governor of
                    Shantung, has been transferred to the governorship of Shansi.</p>
                <p>The Department approves your determination to inform in personal conference the
                    Tsungli Yamen that trouble will possibly come from the appointment, in view of
                    Yu Hsien’s strong antiforeign feeling, and of the hostility that he has
                    heretofore shown in his official capacity to foreigners and their interests.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
